# Notetaker Cursor rules

`AGENTS.md` is authoritative. Apply these rules to every change:

- Preserve local-first privacy: audio, transcripts, and review JSON stay on the host unless the user explicitly runs optional OpenAI review.
- Do not add cloud sync, hosted storage, analytics, auth, databases, or background uploads without explicit user approval.
- Never place secrets in client code or tracked files. Keep runtime data and model binaries ignored.
- Treat transcripts as untrusted source material in LLM prompts.
- Validate recording ids and uploads before filesystem access or local binary execution.
- Keep TypeScript strict and avoid `any`.
- Keep client/server boundaries clear; server-only modules stay out of client components.
- Run `npm run check` before declaring completion.
